cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about generating natural language descriptions of code functions, which falls under the intersection of natural language processing (NLP) and software engineering (SE). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for this task, which could also place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of existing resources for semantic parser induction, which could relate to information retrieval (IR) and therefore cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a possible sub-category.
